Class BlastPlus

  • java.lang.Object

    Enables (command line) interaction with BLAST+

    Current usage is for blast searches and auto-annotation support

      • runBlast

        public static HashMap<String,SearchResult> runBlast(BlastQuery query)
                                             throws BlastException
        Run a blast query using the following output format options
        • stitle - subject title
        • qstart - query match start index
        • qend - query match end index
        • sstart - subject match start index
        • send
        • sstrand
        • evalue
        • bitscore
        • length - alignment length
        • nident - number of identical matches
        Parameters:
        query - wrapper around blast query
        Returns:
        map of unique entry identifier (whose sequence was a subject) to the search result hit details
        Throws:
        BlastException

      • processFeaturesBlastOutput

        public static List<DNAFeature> processFeaturesBlastOutput(String blastOutput)
        Process the output of the blast run for features into a list of feature objects
        Expected format for the output (per line) is feature_id, label, type, qstart, qend, sstart, send, sstrand Therefore line[0] is feature_id, line[1] is label etc
        Since we are only interested in features that have a full match (covers entire feature) some matches are manually eliminated. The results returned by blast can cover only a subset of the sequence. e.g. given query = 'ATGC' and feature1 = 'ATG' and feature2 = 'TATGT', the query will return 1,3,1,3 and 1,3,2,4.
        Parameters:
        blastOutput - blast program output
        Returns:
        list of feature objects resulting from processing the blast output

      • rebuildDatabase

        public static void rebuildDatabase(boolean force)
                            throws BlastException
        Re-builds the blast database, using a lock file to prevent concurrent rebuilds. The lock file has a "life-span" of 1 day after which it is deleted.

        Also, a rebuild can be forced even if a lock file exists which is less than a day old

        Parameters:
        force - set to true to force a rebuild. Use with caution
        Throws:
        BlastException

        Run the bl2seq program on multiple subjects.
